decks.notes: This deck focuses on using powerful spells and card advantage to control the game, while also utilizing powerful companions like Lurrus of the Dream-Den to gain additional value. It runs a suite of classic control elements such as counterspells like Force of Will and removal like Swords to Plowshares, alongside powerful draw spells like Ancestral Recall and Dig Through Time. The deck also includes disruptive creatures like Lavinia, Azorius Renegade to slow down opponents, and card selection tools like Brainstorm and Ponder to ensure consistency in draws.

This Vintage 1 vs 1 Aggro - Hatebear deck focuses on disrupting opponents' strategies by playing hate cards like Thalia, Guardian of Thraben and Archon of Emeria, while also utilizing efficient creatures like Seasoned Dungeoneer and White Plume Adventurer to apply pressure. The deck also includes disruptive artifacts like Chalice of the Void and Trinisphere, along with land destruction from Wasteland and Strip Mine. With a mix of hate cards, aggro creatures, and disruptive elements, this deck aims to control the game and secure a victory through strategic play and resource denial.

The deck focuses on utilizing artifact-based combos to generate massive amounts of mana and card advantage. By bouncing multiple artifacts back to hand with Paradoxical Outcome, players can draw into key pieces like Tinker or Time Vault to set up game-winning plays. The inclusion of cards like The One Ring and Coveted Jewel provide additional win conditions and utility. The deck also includes disruptive elements like Force of Will and Trinisphere to control the game and protect key pieces. Overall, the deck aims to create overwhelming board states and win the game quickly through powerful combo plays.

This deck focuses on utilizing Underworld Breach to establish a powerful combo strategy. By utilizing cards like Vexing Bauble, Psychic Frog, and Orcish Bowmasters to generate card advantage and control the opponent's board, the deck aims to set up a winning combination of spells like Wheel of Fortune, Timetwister, and Brainstorm to overwhelm the opponent. With a suite of powerful mana acceleration cards like Moxen, Lotus, and fetch lands, the deck can quickly assemble its combo pieces and close out the game. The inclusion of disruptive elements like Flusterstorm and Force of Will helps protect the combo and ensure its success.
